It was believed the old lady may have climbed out of it.

433
00:27:02,820 --> 00:27:05,150
我告诉法庭监守
I told the bailiff

434
00:27:05,160 --> 00:27:06,620
就在我离开房间之前
Right before I left her in the room,

435
00:27:06,630 --> 00:27:08,790
她问我她哪有好喝的水
she asked me where she could get a good drink of water,

436
00:27:08,810 --> 00:27:11,210
我回答她田纳西州有
and I told her Tennessee.

437
00:27:13,350 --> 00:27:16,100
格英丝夫人再也没有出现在梅塔莫拉
Mrs. Goings was seen no more in Metamora.

438
00:27:16,120 --> 00:27:18,260
正义得到了伸张
Enough justice had been done.

439
00:27:18,540 --> 00:27:20,850
甚至没人向担保人要保释金
They even forgave the bondsman her bail.

440
00:27:22,550 --> 00:27:24,800
我恐怕不太  我断定
- I'm afraid I don't see - I decided

441
00:27:26,530 --> 00:27:29,160
宪法赋予我开战的权力
that the Constitution gives me war powers,

442
00:27:30,540 --> 00:27:33,610
可没人知道那究竟是何种权力
but no one knows just exactly what those powers are.

443
00:27:34,780 --> 00:27:37,790
有人说它不存在  我不知道  我坚信
Some say they don't exist. I don't know. I decided,

444
00:27:37,890 --> 00:27:39,560
我需要它们的存在
I needed them to exist to

445
00:27:39,560 --> 00:27:42,410
以坚守我保护宪法的誓言
uphold my oath to protect the Constitution,

446
00:27:42,770 --> 00:27:44,170
所以我决定
which I decided meant that

447
00:27:44,170 --> 00:27:46,470
我可以把反叛者的奴隶
I could take the rebels' slaves from 'em as

