00:49:30,300 --> 00:49:32,620
时间会说明一切的  威廉
Time is a great thickener of things, William.

855
00:49:32,650 --> 00:49:34,530
是啊  我也觉得
Yes, I suppose it is.

856
00:49:34,800 --> 00:49:37,400
我都不知道你说这些干什么
Actually I have no idea what you mean by that.

857
00:49:38,990 --> 00:49:40,790
给我弄13张赞成票
Get me thirteen votes.

858
00:49:41,780 --> 00:49:44,460
里士满的家伙还没到呢
Them fellers from Richmond ain't here yet.

859
00:49:57,760 --> 00:50:02,930
美军总部  弗吉尼亚州  1月12日

860
00:50:05,300 --> 00:50:07,700
你在波士顿征了一半的人当兵
You drafted half the men in Boston!

861
00:50:07,880 --> 00:50:10,290
他们的家人会怎么看待我
What do you think their families think about me?

862
00:50:10,600 --> 00:50:12,750
他们没有对我扔东西吐口水
The only reason they don't throw things and spit on me

863
00:50:12,770 --> 00:50:14,120
只是因为你受人爱戴
is 'cause you're so popular.

864
00:50:14,330 --> 00:50:18,270
我无法专心学习英国商业法
I can't concentrate on British mercantile law,

865
00:50:18,280 --> 00:50:20,780
我不关心什么英国商业法
I don't care about British mercantile law.

866
00:50:22,510 --> 00:50:24,160
我都不想成为律师
I might not even want to be a lawyer.

867
00:50:25,900 --> 00:50:28,310
这是个铁饭碗
It's a sturdy profession,

868
00:50:28,740 --> 00:50:30,020
还能让你成为有用之人
and a useful one.

869
00:50:30,040 --> 00:50:34,580
我现在就想成为有用的人  不是等以后
Yes, and I want to be useful, but now, not afterwards!

870
00:50:34,660 --> 00:50:36,420
我可不戴这个  斯莱德先生
I ain't wearing them things, Mr. Slade,

871
00:50:36,420 --> 00:50:37,500
他们从来不搭
they never fit right.

872
00:50:37,540 --> 00:50:39,910
太太想让你戴上它们  别想丢下它
The Mrs. will have you wear 'em. Don't think about leaving 'em.

873
00:50:39,940 --> 00:50:42,290
你在推脱  这是你最喜欢的手段
You're delaying, that's your favorite tactic.

874
00:50:42,400 --> 00:50:43,130
你嘴上不说
You won't tell me no,

875
00:50:43,130 --> 00:50:46,030
但是战争一个月内就会结束  你知道的
but the war will be over in a month, and you know it will!

876
00:50:46,080 --> 00:50:48,610
我觉得预言本身
I've found that prophesying

877
00:50:48,620 --> 00:50:53,020
往往就是最难被预言的事情
is one of life's less prophet-able occupations.

878
00:50:54,730 --> 00:50:56,970
为什么有的黑奴比其他的贵
Why do some slaves cost more than others?

879
00:50:57,020 --> 00:50:58,460
那些还年轻健康的
Ah, if they're still young and healthy,

880
00:50:58,460 --> 00:50:59,640
或者能怀孕的女人  就贵一些
if the women can still conceive, they'll pay more.

881
00:50:59,670 --> 00:51:02,670
把它放回盒子里去  小坏蛋
Put 'em back in the box, you scoundrel.

882
00:51:04,240 --> 00:51:05,200
我们后天要还到
We'll return them to

883
00:51:05,200 --> 00:51:07,250
加德纳先生的工作室去
Mr. Gardner's studio day after next.

884
00:51:08,740 --> 00:51:10,940
小心一点
Be careful with 'em, now.

885
00:51:11,390 --> 00:51:13,230
这手套就不该造出来
These things should've stayed on the calf.

886
00:51:13,260 --> 00:51:16,120
斯莱德先生  您还是奴隶时
When you were a slave, Mr. Slade,

887
00:51:16,120 --> 00:51:17,450
有人打你吗
did they beat you?

888
00:51:17,580 --> 00:51:19,330
我生下来就是自由人
I was born a free man.

889
00:51:19,420 --> 00:51:22,230
有人打我我会立刻还手的
Nobody beat me except I beat them right back.

890
00:51:24,130 --> 00:51:25,780
林肯先生  你能跟我来吗
Mr. Lincoln, could you come with me

891
00:51:25,800 --> 00:51:27,790
凯克莉女士曾是奴隶
Mrs. Keckley was a slave.

892
00:51:27,790 --> 00:51:29,160
问问她被打过吗
Ask her if she was beaten.

893
00:51:29,550 --> 00:51:31,020
你被打过吗  泰德
- Were you? - Tad!

894
00:51:31,730 --> 00:51:34,260
我比你还小时被火铲打过
I was beaten with a fire shovel when I was younger than you.

895
00:51:34,300 --> 00:51:35,640
您该去找林肯太太
You should go to Mrs. Lincoln.

896
00:51:35,640 --> 00:51:36,990
她在威利的房间
She's in Willie's room.

897
00:51:38,090 --> 00:51:39,050
她从不去那里
She never goes in there.

898
00:51:39,080 --> 00:51:41,780
迎接队列已经在门口站好了
The reception line is already stretching out the door.

899
00:51:45,440 --> 00:51:47,730
这地方15岁以上65岁以下
See, I'll be the only man over fifteen and under sixty-five

900
00:51:47,750 --> 00:51:50,000
没穿军装的就只有我了
in this whole place not in uniform.

901
00:51:50,070 --> 00:51:51,450
我不到15岁
I'm under fifteen.

902
00:52:12,200 --> 00:52:14,610
我头很疼
My head hurts so.

903
00:52:17,740 --> 00:52:20,340
威利死的那晚  我祈求一同死去
I prayed for death the night Willie died.

904
00:52:21,480 --> 00:52:24,480
头痛让我知道我没能如愿
The headaches are how I know I didn't get my wish.

905
00:52:27,440 --> 00:52:32,420
如何才能从白天熬到黑夜
How to endure the long afternoon that go deep into the night.

906
00:52:32,470 --> 00:52:33,520
我知道
I know.

907
00:52:33,680 --> 00:52:37,000
如何才能不去想他  我怎么做得到
Trying not to think about him. How will I manage?

908
00:52:37,050 --> 00:52:39,140
总能做到的  能做到
- Somehow you will. -Somehow.

909
00:52:41,050 --> 00:52:44,050
总能做到的  能做到的
Somehow. Somehow. Somehow

910
00:52:44,300 --> 00:52:47,160
每次派对  每次
Every party, every

911
00:52:53,340 --> 00:52:57,720
在这房子的四年里时刻在谴责我们
Four years more in this terrible house reproaching us.

912
00:52:59,790 --> 00:53:02,000
他病得很厉害
He was a very sick little boy.

913
00:53:02,040 --> 00:53:04,690
我们应该取消那个招待会  不是吗
We should've cancelled that reception, shouldn't we?

914
00:53:04,720 --> 00:53:07,650
我们不知道他病得多重  我知道
- We didn't know how sick he was. - I knew, I knew

915
00:53:08,750 --> 00:53:11,150
那晚我亲眼看到他奄奄一息
I saw that night he was dying.

916
00:53:11,220 --> 00:53:14,810
三年前  战事正不断升级
Three years ago, the war was going so badly,

917
00:53:14,810 --> 00:53:17,090
我们必须抛开情感强行振作
and we had to put on a face.

918
00:53:17,440 --> 00:53:20,690
我看着威利死去  玛丽
- But I saw Willie was dying. - Mary.

919
00:53:20,730 --> 00:53:22,120
我就这么眼睁睁看着  听我说
- I saw him. - Listen.

920
00:53:25,010 --> 00:53:27,360
这对你来说很难
It's too hard.

921
00:53:32,380 --> 00:53:33,780
太难了
Too hard.

922
00:53:47,910 --> 00:53:51,870
招待会  1月15日

923
00:53:55,770 --> 00:53:57,670
她只有10尺远
She's just ten feet yonder.

924
00:53:57,670 --> 00:53:58,750
我可不想丢了饭碗
I'd like to keep my job.

925
00:54:00,500 --> 00:54:03,770
萨姆纳议员  好久不见
Senator Sumner, it has been much too long.

926
00:54:03,840 --> 00:54:06,030
您真是美艳动人
Oh, who can look on that celestial face and

927
00:54:06,050 --> 00:54:07,620
这位是詹姆斯・阿什利  女士
- And - James Ashley, ma'am,

928
00:54:08,030 --> 00:54:09,920
感谢上苍  感谢上苍 我们见过几次
We've met several times. Praise Heavens, praise Heavens,

929
00:54:09,960 --> 00:54:12,220
我还以为今晚会十分无趣呢
just when I had abandoned hope of amusement,

930
00:54:12,230 --> 00:54:14,630
这不是众议院筹款委员会主席吗
It's the Chairman of the House Ways and Means Committee!

931
00:54:14,810 --> 00:54:15,950
林肯太太
Mrs. Lincoln.

932
00:54:16,110 --> 00:54:18,510
请称呼我第一夫人
Madame President if you please.

933
00:54:18,740 --> 00:54:23,540
千万别派下属委员会来调查我
Oh, don't convene another subcommittee to investigate me, sir!

934
00:54:23,560 --> 00:54:24,130
我开玩笑呢
I'm teasing!

935
00:54:24,130 --> 00:54:25,350
笑一个  韦德议员
Smile, Senator Wade.

936
00:54:25,370 --> 00:54:27,450
我这就是在笑呢  林肯太太
I believe I am smiling, Mrs. Lincoln.

937
00:54:27,490 --> 00:54:30,390
只要您家的财务没什么问题  夫人
As long as your household accounts are in order, Madame,

938
00:54:30,470 --> 00:54:32,880
我们就不需要调查它们
we'll have no need to investigate them.

939
00:54:32,940 --> 00:54:35,920
你一直都对我家的账本
You have always taken such a lively,

940
00:54:35,980 --> 00:54:39,860
有着强烈的检察兴趣
even prosecutorial interest in my household accounts.

941
00:54:39,900 --> 00:54:42,300
那是因为您家的账务让人感兴趣
Your household accounts have always been so interesting.

942
00:54:42,450 --> 00:54:44,850
谢谢  这倒是真的
Yes, thank you, it's true,

943
00:54:45,120 --> 00:54:49,150
摆平农务和伙食的账务可真是奇迹
the miracles I have wrought out of fertilizer bills and cutlery invoices,

944
00:54:49,150 --> 00:54:51,570
不过我必须做到
but I had to!

945
00:54:53,140 --> 00:54:55,040
四年前  当我和总统到这里时
Four years ago, when the president and I arrived,

946
00:54:55,040 --> 00:54:56,750
这里跟猪窝一样
this was pure pigsty.

947
00:54:56,830 --> 00:54:58,660
土耳其地毯上尽是烟草污渍
Tobacco stains in the turkey carpets.

948
00:54:58,690 --> 00:55:02,030
天花板上长着月光般泛绿的蘑菇
Mushrooms, green as the moon, sprouting from the ceilings!

949
00:55:02,140 --> 00:55:05,430
还有少得可怜的维护预算
And a pauper's pittance allotted for improvements.

950
00:55:05,760 --> 00:55:10,410
似乎你们委员会同全华盛顿一起
As if your committee joined with all of Washington awaiting,

951
00:55:10,410 --> 00:55:14,180
在这个你们期待成为我们舒适归宿的肮脏小窝里
in what you anticipated would be our comfort in squalor,

952
00:55:14,180 --> 00:55:18,610
等着证明我们是来自草原的原始人
further proove that my husband and I were prairie primitives,

953
00:55:18,610 --> 00:55:21,710
因人民选择的错误和民主制度的瑕疵
unsuited to the position to which an error of the people,

954
00:55:21,710 --> 00:55:23,930
被推举到一个我们配不上的高位
a flaw in the democratic process, had elevated us.

955
00:55:24,360 --> 00:55:27,290
过去就让它过去吧  新的一年到了
The past is the past, it's a new year now,

956
00:55:27,380 --> 00:55:31,360
听说我们相处得还不错
and we are all getting along, or so they tell me.

957
00:55:31,640 --> 00:55:33,720
我们要同心协力
I gather we are working together!

958
00:55:33,870 --> 00:55:35,830
白宫和其他机构
The White House and the other House,

959
00:55:35,830 --> 00:55:37,530
共同出谋划策
hatching little plans together.

960
00:55:37,570 --> 00:55:38,360
母亲  怎么了
- Mother? - What?

961
00:55:38,390 --> 00:55:40,150
人都堵在这了
You're creating a bottleneck.

962
00:55:40,590 --> 00:55:42,690
我耽搁您太久了
Oh, I'm detaining you.

963
00:55:43,160 --> 00:55:46,300
或者说  我耽搁您身后的人们太久了
And more importantly, the people behind you.

964
00:55:46,690 --> 00:55:49,600
人民爱戴我的丈夫
How the people love my husband,

965
00:55:49,880 --> 00:55:54,180
他们成群结队在公众日来看他
they flock to see him by their thousands on public days!

966
00:55:54,370 --> 00:55:56,770
他们永远不会像爱他一样爱您
They will never love you the way they love him.

967
00:55:58,700 --> 00:56:01,100
知道这些您一定很难受
How difficult it must be for you to know that.

968
00:56:01,980 --> 00:56:04,380
但是记住这些也很重要
And yet how important to remember it.

969
00:56:15,000 --> 00:56:18,000
明天的辩论中轮到我们发言
Since we have the floor next in the debate,

970
00:56:18,020 --> 00:56:20,420
我建议你或许
I thought I'd suggest you might

971
00:56:20,990 --> 00:56:22,730
缓和一下你的脾气
temper your contributions

972
00:56:22,730 --> 00:56:26,010
免得吓到了保守派的朋友们
so as not to frighten our conservative friends?

973
00:56:26,120 --> 00:56:30,090
阿什利说你在收买边缘的民主党人
Ashley insists you're ensuring approval by dispensing patronage

974
00:56:30,150 --> 00:56:33,150
来保证修正案通过
to otherwise undeserving Democrats.

975
00:56:33,210 --> 00:56:34,370
如果你要用土地挪用
I can't ensure a single damn thing

976
00:56:34,370 --> 00:56:36,250
革命审判和惩罚
if you scare the whole House

977
00:56:36,290 --> 00:56:38,360
吓唬整个议会的话
with talk of land appropriations,

978
00:56:38,360 --> 00:56:40,620
我就什么都保证不了了
revolutionary tribunals, punitive

979
00:56:40,650 --> 00:56:44,660
等战争结束  我想争取完全的平等
When the war ends, I intend to push for full equality,

980
00:56:44,660 --> 00:56:47,910
赋予黑人选举权  当然远不只如此
the Negro vote, and much more.

981
00:56:48,540 --> 00:56:51,770
国会将收复每一寸叛军土地
Congress shall mandate the seizure of every foot of rebel land

982
00:56:51,820 --> 00:56:54,540
和他们的所有财产
and every dollar of their property.

983
00:56:55,870 --> 00:56:57,910
我们要用充公的财富
We'll use their confiscated wealth

984
00:56:57,910 --> 00:57:00,850
去建立成千上万黑人农民阶级
to establish hundreds of thousands of free Negro farmers,

985
00:57:00,880 --> 00:57:06,220
和武装力量去占领和转换叛徒的遗产
and at their side soldiers armed to occupy and transform the heritage of traitors.

986
00:57:07,240 --> 00:57:08,610
我们要建立一片
We'll build up a land down there

987
00:57:08,610 --> 00:57:11,750
属于自由的男女老少的自由之地
of free men and free women and free children and freedom.

988
00:57:13,500 --> 00:57:15,900
国家要知道我们的计划
The nation needs to know that we have such plans.

989
00:57:17,450 --> 00:57:20,450
这是未加修饰的战后重建计划
That's the untempered version of reconstruction.

990
00:57:22,440 --> 00:57:26,990
跟我想的不太一样
It's not quite exactly what I intend,

991
00:57:29,020 --> 00:57:32,480
我们早晚会反对彼此的政见
but we shall oppose one another in the course of time.

992
00:57:32,700 --> 00:57:34,850
但现在我们在同一条战线  所以我请求你
Now we're working together, and I'm asking you

993
00:57:34,890 --> 00:57:36,000
耐心点  对吧
for patience, I expect.

994
00:57:36,030 --> 00:57:37,640
当人民意见不一致
When the people disagree,

995
00:57:37,640 --> 00:57:39,360
就需要慢慢让他们
bringing them together requires going slow

996
00:57:39,370 --> 00:57:40,660
能够达成一致
till they're ready to make up.

997
00:57:40,700 --> 00:57:42,030
去他的人民
Ah, shit on the people,

998
00:57:42,040 --> 00:57:43,640
他们要什么  他们准备怎么样
and what they want, and what they're ready for,

999
00:57:43,660 --> 00:57:46,240
我才不管他们要什么
I don't give a goddamn about the people and what they want!

1000
00:57:46,390 --> 00:57:49,690
这是一个长期为了人民的利益奋斗
This is the face of someone who has fought long and hard for the good of the people

1001
00:57:49,700 --> 00:57:52,120
却从不关心人民的人的面庞
without caring much for any of 'em.

1002
00:57:53,210 --> 00:57:55,610
我不带假发看起来更糟糕
And I look a lot worse without my wig.

1003
00:57:56,200 --> 00:57:59,640
人民选举了我  去代表他们
The people elected me! To represent them!

1004
00:57:59,820 --> 00:58:02,960
去领导他们  我成功领了他们  你应该试试
To lead them! And I lead! You ought to try it!

1005
00:58:05,180 --> 00:58:08,530
我欣赏你的热情  史蒂文斯先生
I admire your zeal, Mr. Stevens,

1006
00:58:08,550 --> 00:58:11,750
我也试过从中牟利
and I have tried to profit from the example of it.

1007
00:58:13,430 --> 00:58:16,830
如果听了你的  在萨穆特要塞战役
If I've listened to you,  I've declared every slave free

1008
00:58:16,830 --> 00:58:18,450
打响时就宣布奴隶解放
the minute the first shell struck Fort Sumter.

1009
00:58:18,550 --> 00:58:21,160
那么边境州将投向叛军
Then the border states would've gone over to the confederacy,

1010
00:58:21,250 --> 00:58:23,770
我们将输掉战争  失去联盟
the war would've been lost and the Union along with it,

1011
00:58:23,850 --> 00:58:25,840
不仅不能像我们预期那样
and instead of abolishing slavery,

1012
00:58:25,840 --> 00:58:27,620
在两周内废除奴隶制
as we hope to do in two weeks,

1013
00:58:27,740 --> 00:58:30,000
我们将无助地看着
we'll be watching helpless as infants as it spread

1014
00:58:30,010 --> 00:58:32,550
美国南部分裂出去
from the American South into South America.

1015
00:58:32,610 --> 00:58:35,020
你很渴望对我说这些吧
Oh God, how you have longed to say that to me.

1016
00:58:36,340 --> 00:58:37,820
你说你信任他们
You claim you trust them.

1017
00:58:37,830 --> 00:58:40,590
可你知道人民是什么样子
But you know what the people are.

1018
00:58:41,180 --> 00:58:44,730
在白人的心里本该引导他们的灵魂
You know that the inner compass

1019
00:58:44,730 --> 00:58:46,630
通往正义的罗盘
that should direct the soul toward justice

1020
00:58:46,730 --> 00:58:50,790
已经被邪恶的奴隶制
has ossified in white men and women, north and south, unto utter uselessness

1021
00:58:50,790 --> 00:58:54,390
僵化得毫无用处了
through tolerating the evil of slavery.

1022
00:58:54,450 --> 00:58:57,060
白人不能容忍
White people cannot bear the thought of sharing

1023
00:58:57,070 --> 00:58:59,850
与黑人共享这个国家无尽财富的想法
this country's infinite abundance with Negroes.

